message.content: They followed him to a city bus stop on Cailing Avenue, where he waited. The bus stop was a deserted island on a empty street. But not for long, for soon pedestrians and cars flocked upon the Avenue from its many tributary streets. It might have been a normal business-day hustle, except for two anomalies. First, it was Sunday morning; and, second, everyone walked, or drove, or waited as a person possessed of a single all-exclusive purpose.
